722352f.text:
1001 to O7 Park Avenue, at, adjoining and north of the N. E. corner of East 84th Street, as photographed forming a background for a truck snow plow. East 84th Street is on the right and the corner building is No. 1001. The two frame buildings are to the north of same. Note the fenced area in the center of Park Avenue,
divinding traffic into two lanes.
About 1925
Views 1,2
Gift of Albert A. Volk Co.

722354f-a.text:
Park Avenue, at north east corner of 84th Street, showing four
houses to be demolished in 1928.
Hos. 1003 and 1005, the small ones in the middle, are the last two freme houses on Park Avenue below 100th Street. See Underhill's larger photograph of the same corner May 1928
before demolition.
November 19, 1927.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.
Neg #671
